101
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:59,699
Uh, someone just asked me to take care of it!

102
00:06:01,622 --> 00:06:05,8
Aah! Hey! Anna!

103
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:08,65
Why don't we-

104
00:06:11,476 --> 00:06:12,336
Aah!

105
00:06:12,336 --> 00:06:13,990
Shadow X, stealth mode on!

106
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:17,147
What is it? Why are you doing that?

107
00:06:17,147 --> 00:06:19,277
There was just a huge bug!

108
00:06:19,277 --> 00:06:24,95
Theo, you hate bugs, right? I know!

109
00:06:24,95 --> 00:06:26,655
So Anna, what brings you here?

110
00:06:26,655 --> 00:06:27,699
Oh, that's right!

111
00:06:30,944 --> 00:06:33,507
Now, you can open your eyes...

112
00:06:35,944 --> 00:06:38,6
Happy birthday, Jun!

113
00:06:44,388 --> 00:06:49,854
Thank you, Anna! I never imagined you'd come to celebrate my birthday!

114
00:06:49,854 --> 00:06:52,395
Hey, time to blow out the candles!

115
00:06:54,908 --> 00:06:57,465
Jun. Calling Jun.

116
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:00,396
What's that sound?

117
00:07:00,396 --> 00:07:02,561
Yeah, what's that?

118
00:07:02,561 --> 00:07:05,191
It must be the TV in the living room!

119
00:07:05,191 --> 00:07:09,98
I think we have to open the street now. Will that be okay?

120
00:07:09,98 --> 00:07:10,330
Jun?

121
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:12,539
Jun! I need a reply!

122
00:07:12,539 --> 00:07:15,538
Jun! Jun! Jun!

123
00:07:15,538 --> 00:07:17,566
Stop saying my name, please!

124
00:07:17,566 --> 00:07:19,437
H-happy birthday, Jun!

125
00:07:19,986 --> 00:07:22,238
Jun! Why isn't he replying?

126
00:07:22,238 --> 00:07:24,269
What? What's the matter?

127
00:07:26,285 --> 00:07:29,402
Maybe he has been taken hostage by robbers!

128
00:07:31,477 --> 00:07:33,464
Jun! I'll be there soon!

129
00:07:34,473 --> 00:07:35,943
Blue Cop!

130
00:07:53,562 --> 00:07:54,902
What was that?

131
00:07:55,32 --> 00:07:57,48
It sounded like an accident!

132
00:07:57,48 --> 00:07:59,212
Anyway, let's blow out the candles!

133
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:01,225
Yes! Let's sing the birthday song!

134
00:08:01,225 --> 00:08:03,257
1, 2, 3!

135
00:08:03,257 --> 00:08:07,599
Happy birthday to me...

136
00:08:17,987 --> 00:08:19,959
What's that?!

137
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:26,468
No... this looks really bad!

138
00:08:26,468 --> 00:08:28,581
Don't stand there watching! Give them a hand!

139
00:08:29,721 --> 00:08:32,240
What do we do? Jun! Hurry, give us a command!

140
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:35,652
Jun?!

141
00:08:35,652 --> 00:08:38,806
You're hiding something from me, aren't you?!

142
00:08:38,806 --> 00:08:40,910
But, I...

143
00:08:40,910 --> 00:08:42,179
I'm done!

144
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,561
Ah, no! Anna!

145
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,569
Hello...

146
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,391
Aah!!

147
00:08:59,345 --> 00:09:01,733
She just found out...

148
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,717
The secret is out...

149
00:09:07,821 --> 00:09:09,000
So you guys are like...

150
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:15,110
refugees who came to Earth all the way from planet Machina at the end of the galaxy?

151
00:09:15,110 --> 00:09:16,673
Oh...

152
00:09:16,673 --> 00:09:18,92
She's smart.

153
00:09:18,286 --> 00:09:21,547
So, Anna. Will you help us keep these guys a secret, please?

154
00:09:21,626 --> 00:09:23,264
I'm afraid not.

155
00:09:23,264 --> 00:09:24,958
Huh? Why not?

156
00:09:24,958 --> 00:09:28,603
Because this is... the first encounter between humanity and aliens.

157
00:09:28,603 --> 00:09:31,555
This is not something us kids can handle by ourselves.

158
00:09:31,555 --> 00:09:32,960
But I'm a grown-up.

159
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,460
I'm sorry, Mister Edo.

160
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:36,831
Wait, please stop calling me Mister...

161
00:09:36,831 --> 00:09:40,261
Anna. We just want to live quietly on planet Earth.

162
00:09:40,261 --> 00:09:41,736
Please trust us.

163
00:09:41,736 --> 00:09:44,235
It's not that I don't trust you. I just think...

164
00:09:44,235 --> 00:09:48,697
that we won't be able to keep lying to the grown ups.

165
00:09:51,278 --> 00:09:52,993
Hey, it's my dad!

166
00:09:53,598 --> 00:09:55,983
Dad? The father of this child!

167
00:09:55,983 --> 00:09:57,884
There are people who are grown-ups?

168
00:09:57,884 --> 00:10:01,7
Anna's dad is the grown-up who is in charge of important things.

169
00:10:01,7 --> 00:10:02,847
He's the mayor of Mowtown!

170
00:10:02,847 --> 00:10:03,939
Shh...

171
00:10:05,684 --> 00:10:07,434
Hello, daddy!

172
00:10:07,885 --> 00:10:10,478
Anna, where are you?

173
00:10:11,92 --> 00:10:13,460
...he's asking where I am!

174
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:15,22
Why is he asking?

175
00:10:15,22 --> 00:10:17,458
Could it be... he found out that you're with us?

176
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:19,320
No, that's not possible!

177
00:10:19,627 --> 00:10:22,320
He's not a mind reader. How would he know?

178
00:10:22,585 --> 00:10:26,29
No, no! My dad really knows everything!

179
00:10:26,29 --> 00:10:29,400
He knew when I skipped piano practice and when I broke a vase!

180
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,595
Yeah! Grown-ups know everything.

181
00:10:31,595 --> 00:10:34,555
Yeah, you can't lie to them, you know.

182
00:10:34,555 --> 00:10:38,300
Hang on! You mean, the mayor already knows?

183
00:10:38,757 --> 00:10:41,182
About us Metal Cardbots on Earth?

